title: 820-00928 20V wont boot
message:
Board from another shop with previous repair attempt.

L4004 burn out and has been replaced with jumper and PP5V_S0_ALSCAM_F got 0.380V in diode mode.
There is some liquid damage around U7370, U7220.
There was some work with U7220, U7210/20.

Diode mode on big coils is 0.002V-0.004V.
Removed U7220, U7210/20 and diode mode reading on big coils are still the same.

Any idea what next to check?

title: 820-00928 20V wont boot
message:
Switch to ohm scale for very low readings in diode mode.
And compare values with good board.
CPU has low values as normal, depending on model.
